This paper combines data from Google Correlate and Google Trends with ground truth data from the American Community Survey to derive new insights into fertility and its meaning. The paper uses machine learning techniques to build predictive models of regional variation in fertility and explores if aggregated web search data can also be used to model fertility trends. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SD (Software Development), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences).
